The remains of former Bendel Insurance goalkeeper, Umar Ahmad Jalingo has been buried according to Islamic rites in Gombe. Jalingo who until his death was one of Insurance goalkeepers, died in the early hours of yesterday barely two days after he was discharged for an undisclosed ailment at the Federal Teaching Hospital, Gombe. The head coach of Bendel Insurance, Bernard Ogbe who broke the news said Jalingo is survived by his wife and four children and that the late goalkeeperr who also played for Gombe United has been buried. The statement from Bendel Insurance media read: “We are sad to announce the passing away of one of our Goalkeepers,Umar Ahmad Jalingo. The deceased player’s family source broke the sad news to Insurance Manager Bernard Ogbe this morning (yesterday).